  <div class="poem-body">
    <div class="poem-epigraph">Written on a platform in February. The train was late.</div>
    <div class="poem-stanza">
      <span class="poem-line">You arrive and I am already</span>
      <span class="poem-line">half gone, coat on, bag at my feet,</span>
      <span class="poem-line">which is how I love most things —</span>
      <span class="poem-line gold">ready to leave before they start.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="poem-stanza">
      <span class="poem-line">The platform empties around me.</span>
      <span class="poem-line">A pigeon walks the yellow line</span>
      <span class="poem-line">as if it knows the rule</span>
      <span class="poem-line">does not apply to it.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="poem-stanza">
      <span class="poem-line">I have not been north in three years.</span>
      <span class="poem-line">What I am returning to</span>
      <span class="poem-line">is not a place</span>
      <span class="poem-line gold">but the person I was when I left it.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="poem-stanza">
      <span class="poem-line">The train arrives on time.</span>
      <span class="poem-line">I do not get on.</span>
      <span class="poem-line">I stand there a moment longer,</span>
      <span class="poem-line">watching it go.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

